The paper deals with the representation of planar graphs, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). It also involves algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) for computing the representation. The concept of 1-planarity is related to graph theory (cs.DM) and the paper discusses the density of 1-visible and 1-planar graphs. The paper also mentions the concept of crossing numbers, which is a topic in graph theory and geometric topology (cs.GT). Finally, the paper discusses the practical applications of the 1-visibility representation, which falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
